President Biden has directed federal agencies to provide resources to Florida as Hurricane Ian approaches. He has held calls with Governor Ron DeSantis and mayors from various cities to discuss preparations. FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell has also been in contact with governors from other states. President Biden approved an Emergency Declaration for Florida to support preparedness efforts. FEMA is coordinating with the federal government to assist with state and local preparations. It is pre-staging equipment and resources and pre-positioning federal responders to support emergency response. The administration urges everyone to follow the guidance of local officials.